      "role": "user",
      "content": "Interesting. So, when you talk about the breakdown of \"shared values\" and \"cultural dissonance,\" do you think this implies that certain demographics are inherently less compatible with Western democratic systems compared to others? Like, is there a fundamental difference in how these groups approach governance or social order that makes this shift more volatile?",
